"{\"uid\": \"bangkokpost.com-opinion-opinion-2836087-paris-olympics-can-help-unify-a-fractured-city\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PUBLISHED : 26 Jul 2024 at 04:00 NEWSPAPER SECTION:News WRITER:Lionel Laurent Paris faces the test this week of launching the Olympic Games safely and affordably at a time of war, political polarisation and social unrest.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"04:00 NEWSPAPER SECTION\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"News WRITER\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"the test\", \"from\": 90, \"to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 139}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 171}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 178}, {\"ngram\": \"political polarisation\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"social unrest\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not a done deal.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a done deal\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy-handed security barriers and Covid-style QR codes are already infuriating residents and tourists trying to navigate a River Seine that's been cleaned at great expense.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Heavy-handed security barriers\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 277}, {\"ngram\": \"Covid-style QR codes\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 302}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 349}, {\"ngram\": \"great expense\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet the real challenge will begin once the athletes have packed up and gone home.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the real challenge\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 444}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's greatest city (okay, top five) must complete its gold-medal transformation into something greater: A megalopolis that binds the hipsters, financiers and flaneurs of historic, densely populated Paris to the sprawling regional economy where many Olympic events will actually take place.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world's greatest city\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"its gold-medal transformation\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 605}, {\"ngram\": \"A megalopolis\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"the hipsters\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"financiers\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"flaneurs\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprawling regional economy\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 748}, {\"ngram\": \"many Olympic events\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This would be a more inclusive kind of change than the one Paris has gone through recently.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more inclusive kind\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 837}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mayor Anne Hidalgo's crusade to pedestrianise, modernise and de-motorise swathes of the city has seen road congestion fall and air quality improve but has also made her a divisive figure and irritated commuters who do not make up her core voter base.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pedestrianise\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"modernise\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 950}, {\"ngram\": \"de-motorise swathes\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"her core voter base\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is certainly a thrill in strolling along the banks of the Seine or down car-free Rue de Rivoli -- provided one can block out the roared insults from cyclists who seem to think traffic lights are just there for decoration.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5818152324279654e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a thrill\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"the roared insults\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic lights\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"decoration\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet there have also been missteps, like the embrace of electric scooters that ended up banned last year.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the embrace\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"electric scooters\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gentrification and tourism have also made the city pricier and more exclusive, even as social unrest and bouts of violence have risen.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gentrification\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"tourism\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"the city pricier\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"social unrest\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1579}, {\"ngram\": \"bouts\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post-Brexit influx of bankers and tech types has boosted Paris's soft power, its startup scene and its attraction for AirBnB speculators -- though that bubble has burst somewhat.\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A post-Brexit influx\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"bankers\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"tech types\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"its startup scene\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"its attraction\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"AirBnB speculators\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"that bubble\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cool crowd has migrated eastward to Belleville, away from the un-hip Champs Elysees.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1835, \"end\": 1845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belleville,_Ontario\", \"score\": 0.5795018015811559, \"rank\": 0.3619561515159989, \"text\": \"Belleville\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belleville,_Ontario\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belleville,_Ontario\"}, {\"begin\": 1868, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9918285953529252, \"rank\": 0.008238720428601937, \"text\": \"Champs Elysees\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The cool crowd\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The newly reopened Samaritaine store has become a symbol of Paris's doubling-down on luxury; Bernard Arnault's LVMH is sponsoring the Olympics and chipped in to help repair Notre Dame after a 2019 fire.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Samaritaine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.35374810335145e-43, \"text\": \"Samaritaine\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Samaritaine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Samaritaine\"}, {\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_Arnault\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bernard Arnault\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_Arnault\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_Arnault\"}, {\"begin\": 2057, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Notre-Dame_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.759730093838354e-18, \"text\": \"Notre Dame\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Notre-Dame_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Notre-Dame_de_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"luxury\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1975}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2026}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2019 fire\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From income to accessing services, the gap has grown between Paris's 2 million inhabitants and the 10 million who live in the region.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"income\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2099}, {\"ngram\": \"accessing services\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The centre is gentrifying, while the periphery is getting poorer,\\\" says urbanism expert Laurent Chalard.\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The centre\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"the periphery\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"urbanism expert Laurent Chalard\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have seen this first-hand, having lived on both sides of the peripherique ring road that did away with the city walls but not the psychological barriers of living intra or extra muros.\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this first-hand\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"both sides\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"the peripherique ring road\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2413}, {\"ngram\": \"the city walls\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"not the psychological barriers\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2482}, {\"ngram\": \"living intra\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2498}, {\"ngram\": \"extra muros\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a father of two \\\"inside the walls\\\", I can enjoy the fruits of what really is a 15-minute city: That's how long it takes me to walk to my kids' daycare, my local park, my doctor and my metro stop.\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a father\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2526}, {\"ngram\": \"the walls\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"the fruits\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2576}, {\"ngram\": \"a 15-minute city\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"my kids' daycare\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2668}, {\"ngram\": \"my local park\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2683}, {\"ngram\": \"my doctor\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2694}, {\"ngram\": \"my metro\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But many essential workers live way beyond that radius, priced out by a city that does not build enough housing.\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many essential workers\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"that radius\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2768}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"enough housing\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The walls have gone but segregation remains: A 2019 study found the income gap between the richest and poorest of the Paris region -- those earning \\u20ac4,500 a month (about 176,650 baht) and below \\u20ac900 -- was the biggest in France.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 3055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2945, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3048, \"end\": 3054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998453859, \"rank\": 1.5192405772630194e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The walls\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2836}, {\"ngram\": \"segregation\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"A 2019 study\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"the income gap\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"(about 176,650 baht\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, Europe remains more equal -- and with longer life expectancy -- than the US.\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3141, \"end\": 3143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.9956145220840028, \"rank\": 0.004404795038211833, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3074}, {\"ngram\": \"longer life expectancy\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cities are always going to be places where rich and poor live cheek-by-jowl.\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3221, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cities\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3181}, {\"ngram\": \"jowl\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And gleaming Olympic venues are transforming some areas of Paris, such as the suburb Saint Ouen.\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3281, \"end\": 3286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic venues\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3249}, {\"ngram\": \"some areas\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3277}, {\"ngram\": \"the suburb\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3306}, {\"ngram\": \"Saint Ouen\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, better social and economic cohesion would be good at a time of polarised politics.\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"better social and economic cohesion\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3361}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"polarised politics\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It might address some of the resentment that fuelled last year's rioting and looting in outlying towns like Kylian Mbappe's childhood home of Bondy, where shops and businesses perceived by locals as unaffordable were targeted.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3517, \"end\": 3530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.999999999231477, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kylian Mbappe\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 3551, \"end\": 3556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.499642368813183e-28, \"text\": \"Bondy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the resentment\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3448}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's rioting\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3481}, {\"ngram\": \"looting\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3493}, {\"ngram\": \"outlying towns\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3511}, {\"ngram\": \"shops\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3569}, {\"ngram\": \"businesses\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3584}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carless Parisians would also benefit from smarter integration: Paris depends upon workers coming from outside the city for more than half of its labour force (according to pre-Covid figures), and last year's garbage collectors' strike also showed how dependent it was on incinerator chokepoints beyond the peripherique.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3699, \"end\": 3704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Carless Parisians\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3653}, {\"ngram\": \"smarter integration\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3697}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3725}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3754}, {\"ngram\": \"more than half\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3773}, {\"ngram\": \"its labour force\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3793}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-Covid figures\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3825}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's garbage collectors' strike\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3870}, {\"ngram\": \"incinerator chokepoints\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3930}, {\"ngram\": \"the peripherique\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more cohesive Greater Paris needs to rewire the region, as imagined by ex-president Nicolas Sarkozy in the wake of 2005 urban rioting and the failure to win the 2012 summer games (which went to London).\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 4161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4043, \"end\": 4058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Sarkozy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Sarkozy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Sarkozy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Sarkozy\"}, {\"begin\": 4153, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9995955723409351, \"rank\": 0.0004044438067536155, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A more cohesive Greater Paris\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3986}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4013}, {\"ngram\": \"ex\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4032}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4070}, {\"ngram\": \"2005 urban rioting\", \"from\": 4074, \"to\": 4092}, {\"ngram\": \"the failure\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 summer games\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has already started with the \\\"Grand Paris Express,\\\" a plan to create four new circular metro lines across 200 kilometres of track to connect the suburbs.\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Paris_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grand Paris Express\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Paris_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Paris_Express\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a plan\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4223}, {\"ngram\": \"four new circular metro lines\", \"from\": 4234, \"to\": 4263}, {\"ngram\": \"200 kilometres\", \"from\": 4271, \"to\": 4285}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 4289, \"to\": 4294}, {\"ngram\": \"the suburbs\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a project that has none of the glamour of Baron Haussmann's iconic reshaping of Paris in the 19th century, which gave us landmarks like the Opera Garnier and the wide and airy boulevards that bear his name.\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4366, \"end\": 4381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.510900699115301e-59, \"text\": \"Baron Haussmann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4404, \"end\": 4409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4464, \"end\": 4477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais_Garnier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Opera Garnier\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q24354\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais_Garnier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais_Garnier\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a project\", \"from\": 4324, \"to\": 4333}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4347}, {\"ngram\": \"the glamour\", \"from\": 4351, \"to\": 4362}, {\"ngram\": \"the 19th century\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4429}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4444}, {\"ngram\": \"landmarks\", \"from\": 4445, \"to\": 4454}, {\"ngram\": \"the wide and airy boulevards\", \"from\": 4482, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"his name\", \"from\": 4521, \"to\": 4529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's just as vital if you consider that students will be able to reach their school in half an hour rather than an hour, or that jobs and housing might be redistributed more evenly.\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4716, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"students\", \"from\": 4575, \"to\": 4583}, {\"ngram\": \"their school\", \"from\": 4606, \"to\": 4618}, {\"ngram\": \"half an hour\", \"from\": 4622, \"to\": 4634}, {\"ngram\": \"an hour\", \"from\": 4647, \"to\": 4654}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 4664, \"to\": 4668}, {\"ngram\": \"housing\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A rebalancing is underway...It's a big lever for change,\\\" says geographer Daniel Behar.\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4805, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A rebalancing\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4731}, {\"ngram\": \"a big lever\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4762}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 4767, \"to\": 4773}, {\"ngram\": \"geographer Daniel Behar\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transport links can not do everything, of course.\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transport links\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4822}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 4834, \"to\": 4844}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bigger step towards more joined-up thinking and policy across Greater Paris would be political integration, unifying decision-making for the whole region.\", \"from\": 4857, \"to\": 5015, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bigger step\", \"from\": 4857, \"to\": 4872}, {\"ngram\": \"more joined-up thinking\", \"from\": 4881, \"to\": 4904}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4915}, {\"ngram\": \"Greater Paris\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 4936}, {\"ngram\": \"political integration\", \"from\": 4946, \"to\": 4967}, {\"ngram\": \"decision-making\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4993}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole region\", \"from\": 4998, \"to\": 5014}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That might help more housing projects get off the ground and reduce the likelihood of turf wars between the capital and other local authorities.\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more housing projects\", \"from\": 5032, \"to\": 5053}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 5062, \"to\": 5072}, {\"ngram\": \"the likelihood\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5098}, {\"ngram\": \"turf wars\", \"from\": 5102, \"to\": 5111}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 5120, \"to\": 5131}, {\"ngram\": \"other local authorities\", \"from\": 5136, \"to\": 5159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will also be very difficult to achieve.\", \"from\": 5161, \"to\": 5203, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, we may be just a few years away from a more efficient regional engine responsible for 30% of France's economic output.\", \"from\": 5205, \"to\": 5330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5305, \"end\": 5311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998453859, \"rank\": 1.5192405772630194e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more efficient regional engine\", \"from\": 5249, \"to\": 5281}, {\"ngram\": \"30%\", \"from\": 5298, \"to\": 5301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the meantime, though, Paris needs to navigate the Olympics and choppy political waters.\", \"from\": 5331, \"to\": 5421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5356, \"end\": 5361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.045330562004638e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbped